This paper is about reinforcement learning for recommendation systems, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, it deals with the problem of environment reconstruction with hidden confounders, which is a common issue in real-world applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also proposes a multi-agent generative adversarial imitation learning framework, which could potentially fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
